import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { UserStore } from "./UserStore"
import { Playground, PropsTable } from "docz"

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"user-store"}}>{`User Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"store"}}>{`Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"hierarchy"}}>{`Hierarchy`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This store gains access to the user, department, boxes, and folders and is accessed in that order. The user object encompasses everything beneath it. Through the user, you can access the user's departments. Through the departments, you can access boxes assigned to that department; through the boxes, you can access the folders.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Some decisions are made here depending on whether or not the user has access to more than one department.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`A user cannot see or access departments that they do not have access to.`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
